Description: A session-based engine for Cognitive Diagnostic Computerized 
    Adaptive Testing (CD-CAT). Supports DINA, DINO, and GDINA models with 
    item selection criteria including KL, PWKL, MPWKL, and SHE. Provides 
    MAP, MLE, and EAP attribute estimation, content balancing, exposure 
    control, and shadow CAT via constraint functions. Designed for 
    real-time item-by-item adaptive applications.
